üîµ Data story 1: When is the pandamic wave in Israel ?
üîµ Data story 2: Why high vaccination rate still cause high cases?

Conclusion üìç
Reference üìñ




Jerusalem,IsraelIntroduction üí°
Israel is a small, narrow country (with continually disputed borders), located in Western Asia. Its size is comparable to the state of Maryland. Israel has an amazing diversity of landscape, including mountains, desert, and a fertile river valley, where you can find the most famous Dead Sea. The capital of Israel is the holy city ‚Äì Jerusalem, which is full of the historic and religious elements that make this city so special.






Background information about COVID-19 in Israel ü¶†
The first COVID-19 case in Israel was found in February 21, 2020. Now the pandemic has caused four waves in Israel in February 2020, September 2020, January 2021 and August 2021 separately. The government has already taken actions on policies and restrictions. There are 8789776 people in Israel. In this pandemic, there are 1,165,682 cases and 7,338 deaths in total until September 11, 2021.
Data description üìé
There are two dataset of this analysis. The first dataset is from Our world in data, where contains all countries‚Äô COVID data. And I filter the Israel related information, where the range of the data is from February 20, 2020 to September 11, 2021. The dataset records the total cases, new cases, total deaths, new deaths, vaccinations, date and population.
Another dataset is about weekly cases and weekly test of different age groups and genders in Israel. The dataset is from Data Gov of Israel. Part of the data is recorded by Hebrew language, I recode some information with English for better analysis.
COVID-19 analysis in Israel üå°Ô∏è

The graph compares the male and female in Israel of being new COVID cases. Although there are some missing data here, it can clear see the four pandemic waves in Israel. Sometimes, the number of cases of female is larger than male. By comparing the numbers, there is no clear evidence that which gender takes the leading role.






Reason 1: The number of weekly new cases of different ages shows that the age between 0 - 19 has the highest infection rate among all the age groups. The numbers of all ages suffer the same trend with the whole country according to the pandemic wave. One of the reason that why young ages has the largest number of cases, is that this group of people is the latest group to get vaccinated. According to Wikipedia, the people between 60 to 70 are the first group to get vaccinated. In this graph it‚Äôs hard to define this group of people. The second largest age group is people between 70 to 74, which in yellow line. The reason is that people are easily to get infected. Other groups of people has good ability of immunity, therefore the cases are not that much.
Reason2: The president approved students‚Äô testing plan during 2021-2022 school year, where students gets infection rate increase to 20%. The curve of People in 0 - 19 also clarifies that why children get such a high number of cases.

Reason3 : In Asia, the United Arab Emirates has the largest vaccination rate with 78%. The red star marks the location of Israel which takes the vaccination rate with 63%. Although, Israel has a great vaccination rate, the neighbor country ‚Äì Palestine with only 9% vaccination rate and Lebanon with only 17% vaccination rate. Thus, people in Israel are easily to get infected though they have taken two doses vaccinations. The Coronavirus has caused other variants like Delta and Lambda which are inherited high infections among people, and this is also the reason why Israel still face the fourth wave. Now, the Israel government are going to take the third dose of vaccinations because the previous immunity is not stronger any more.
Conclusion üìç
Covid-19 has lead to a worldwide pandemic, some countries even faced five or six or even more pandemic waves. Government take actions to restrict people‚Äôs activities and provide more health facilities to encounter this. Israel government also do a great job in facing Covid-19, with high vaccination rate and control everything well. Neighbor countries low vaccination rate and religions problem also make some people are unwilling to get vaccinated, these are the issues of how the govenment need to face in the future. Getting the third dose is one of the ways to do.

articles.title: Ireland COVID-19 report
articles.description: The COVID-19 has lead to a pandamic, this report is based on Ireland.
articles.contents:
Contents
Introduction
Data Description
Data Analysis
What is the daily COVID-19 statistics of Ireland ?
The speed of getting vaccinated
Does increasing cases related to the population ? 

Conclusion
Reference





Introduction
 This is one of my favorite song from Ed Sheeran. He mentioned the Galway which is a city of Ireland and describes his romantic love with his wife, which arrows my interest of the beautiful city of Ireland. Ireland is an island nation located in Western Europe northwest of the United Kingdom. It‚Äôs one of the most beautiful land in the world. I did plan to travel but with the COVID pandemic began, all my plans need to be deferred. This report is mainly about the COVID-19 that happens in Ireland. 
COVID-19 is caused by a Coronavirus called SARS-CoV-2. The virus that causes COVID-19 is spreading very easily and sustainablely between people. The disease has since spread worldwide, leading to an ongoing pandemic. Now the official treatment for this is to take vaccinations. This report mainly focuses on the COVID-19 spread in Ireland, which has 4994724 people. This report will introduce the daily new cases and death of COVID-19, and how the speed of taking vaccinations. All the statistics is between 2020/01/22 and 2021/08/27.
Data Description
The data is from a R package called tidycovid19 where can be download from git with link: Github. And these data is colllected from Our World in Data. I filter the Ireland of the whole dataset as my report. There are 40 variables in this data, I cleaned the data only with 7 variables. And all these information can be see in table1. 
Another dataset is about vaccinations in Ireland, which records the speed of vaccinations. This data is also from Our World in Data. I also choose part of the data and compared the speed of how many people get first dose and total doses in Ireland, there are 6 variables with date, total vaccinations, first and second doses people, population, and I also count the vaccination rate for comparing. 
The third dataset is about the different cities of Ireland, which is from Ireland‚Äôs Open Data portal and collected by Ordnance Survey Ireland. This dataset only records the Covid statistics from February 2020 to May 2021, and I am going to explore part of it.












The latest data shows that in Ireland, there has been 365,313 people are affected by COVID-19 virus, and 5,155 people died of this virus. 23,364 people recovered from this virus. Let‚Äôs move on to the detailed analysis of COVID-19 in Ireland.
Data Analysis
What is the daily COVID-19 statistics of Ireland ?

It‚Äôs a very convenient table for you to measure the COVID impact on Ireland. The horizontal line in January and February of 2020 means there isn‚Äôt many people to be affected by COVID virus. And the new cases fluctuated heavily in the mid of 2020. However, the recover had a steadily increase and the total recovered people is unchanged so the line is also flat. Moreover, both December and July has a increasing trend of new cases, while the death people is really low and some month only got 0 death. Recently, the recovered people all return from hospital, now the hospital resources are enough for people to get cured. Therefore, the line stays the same while goes down to the 0 due to the latest statistics.

This graph draws the daily new cases and new deaths, from the graph we can see that there is an extremely increase since the end of 2020 in December and the new cases got a peak on 2020/01/08 with 8227. Similarly, the number of new death also increases a little in the following days. Moreover, in July of 2021, there is going to be a new pandemic wave of Ireland, since the new cases increases gradually and reach a high position of this year. Compared by the number of new deaths, it seems to under control with lower pressure on hospital and more experience of the government. Or definitely you can guess does the vaccinations work ?

The vaccination has been strongly recommended as one of the effective method to against COVID virus. In Ireland, the spread of vaccination began at the end of 2020, while in January there was the highest increasing then. The speed of getting vaccination is really fast, the blue part is the total vaccinations, the pink part is the first dose vaccination and the green part is the fully doses. The pink line and the green line is getting closer. Until 2021-08-25, the fully vaccination is 3297241 and the total population of Ireland is 4982904. Therefore, the total vaccination rate is 66%. This is in a leading position all over the world.
